      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STAR OF LILY (10) tired late in a very strong contest when third to Bar Jester and Music Time over 1000m in the Clan O'Sullivan at Canberra, on debut four-and-a-half months ago. Fitted with a searching 1000m trial at the Sapphire Coast. Music Time won the Black Opal and then finished third in the Golden Slipper. That form should prove too good for this lot. MAYPORT (5) four-year-old mare by Merchant Navy out of Feels Like Home on debut for the in-form Ible yard. Won her recent trial over 800m at Illawarra Grange. Well drawn and can take a hand in there finish. STEP QUICK (1) placed at Gosford four starts back but struggled since. Returned with an encouraging fourth over 1000m at Orange. Fitter now and the winkers go on. Improver. NOVEL ATTRACTION (6) made an encouraging debut when she chipped away late to finish sixth over 1000m at Queanbeyan. Open to plenty of improvement. ELASAND (3) is deep into the prep and can show a bit more back in trip.",
